The paper focuses on learning communication strategies and control policies for multiple agents, which is a key topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The use of Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) is also mentioned, which suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI. The application of the proposed method to real-world packet routing tasks indicates a potential connection to computer networks (cs.NI). The use of a gating mechanism to prune unprofitable messages suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with the coordination and organization of multiple agents, which could also place it in the category of control systems (cs.SY).
